    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This FD3S-generation RX-7 is a superlative example of Mazda\u2019s lightweight engineering, featuring the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant. The engine maintains factory-spec compression across all rotor faces, with the complex vacuum-solenoid system recently refreshed to ensure seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbochargers. The chassis remains structurally pristine, retaining its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and unperforated aluminum components. Power is delivered through a crisp five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative feedback. From the heat-shielding integrity to the factory-spec bushings, this vehicle exhibits zero mechanical deflection or thermal degradation, representing a true turnkey investment for the discerning collector.",
